<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1241" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1241">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/171a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Canada</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Complaint is made by Huasteca Petroleum Company and Mexican Petroleum
                            Company that, after they have overpaid taxes levied upon oil, Carranza
                            has given orders forbidding shipments of petroleum. He also forbids
                            further operating until a new decree is issued. This will do great
                            injury to the company mentioned and other oil companies. Will you bring
                            the matter to the attention of Carranza and secure what relief you
                            can?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>